# ff8d3e0753124c0f9c08efd217992602
#: ../../c9-implement-security-logging-monitoring.md:17
msgid ""
"The following is a list of security logging implementation best practices."
msgstr ""

# d9b12a02fe95486585abb8165dc5a120
#: ../../c9-implement-security-logging-monitoring.md:19
msgid ""
"Follow a common logging format and approach within the system and across "
"systems of an organization. An example of a common logging framework is the "
"Apache Logging Services which helps provide logging consistency between "
"Java, PHP, .NET,  and C++ applications."
msgstr ""

# 2f3bd348ba06441ea590e0dade309db0
#: ../../c9-implement-security-logging-monitoring.md:20
msgid ""
"Do not log too much or too little. For example, make sure to always log the "
"timestamp and identifying information including the source IP and user-id, "
"but be careful not to log private or confidential data."
msgstr ""

# 0b55215fc3624d3ba7bec2861c3cd8b7
#: ../../c9-implement-security-logging-monitoring.md:21
msgid ""
"Pay close attention to time syncing across nodes to ensure that timestamps "
"are consistent."
msgstr ""

# 8495acd42d334864b1aecedf03c63356
#: ../../c9-implement-security-logging-monitoring.md:24
msgid "Logging for Intrusion Detection and Response"
msgstr ""

# 3f1cdacc55b846ac8d3b16250f899c1c
#: ../../c9-implement-security-logging-monitoring.md:26
msgid ""
"Use logging to identify activity that indicates that a user is behaving "
"maliciously. Potentially malicious activity to log includes:"
